qas.question: Which Spaniard led a battle in 1571?
What battle did the Spanish win in 1571?
In what year did Venice sign a peace treaty with the Ottomans?
After signing a peace treaty with Venice, in what region did the Ottoman empire expand?

context: In southern Europe, a Catholic coalition led by <a0_0>Philip II<a0_0/> of Spain won a victory over the Ottoman fleet at the <a1_0>Battle of Lepanto<a1_0/> (1571). It was a startling, if mostly symbolic, blow to the image of Ottoman invincibility, an image which the victory of the Knights of Malta against the Ottoman invaders in the 1565 <a2_0>Siege of Malta<a2_0/> had recently set about eroding. The battle was far more damaging to the Ottoman navy in sapping experienced manpower than the loss of ships, which were rapidly replaced. The Ottoman navy recovered quickly, persuading Venice to sign a peace treaty in <a3_0>1573<a3_0/>, allowing the Ottomans to expand and consolidate their position in <a4_0>North Africa<a4_0/>.
